{"current_version": "0.1", "project": "S-CORE Baselibs", "project_url": "https://eclipse-score.github.io/baselibs", "versions": {"0.1": {"creator": {"program": "sphinx_needs", "version": "8.0.0"}, "needs": {"comp__baselibs_nothrow": {"belongs_to": ["feat__baselibs"], "belongs_to_back": ["comp_req__nothrow__alloc_fail", "comp_req__nothrow__create", "comp_req__nothrow__mutate_result", "comp_req__nothrow__or_abort", "comp_req__nothrow__pointer_policy", "comp_req__nothrow__asil"], "docname": "nothrow/architecture/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__baselibs_nothrow", "lineno": 25, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Nothrow Component Architecture", "sections": ["Nothrow Component Architecture"], "security": "NO", "status": "invalid", "title": "score::nothrow", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "comp__baselibs_vajson": {"belongs_to": ["feat__baselibs"], "belongs_to_back": ["comp_req__vajson__validation", "comp_req__vajson__trailing_commas", "comp_req__vajson__hex_integers", "comp_req__vajson__unicode", "comp_req__vajson__asil"], "docname": "json/vajson/architecture/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__baselibs_vajson", "lineno": 27, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "VaJson Component Architecture", "sections": ["VaJson Component Architecture"], "security": "YES", "status": "invalid", "title": "VaJson", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "comp_req__nothrow__alloc_fail": {"belongs_to": ["comp__baselibs_nothrow"], "content": "The ``score::nothrow`` memory-resource allocation interfaces shall not throw\non allocation failure and shall instead signal failure by returning\n``nullptr``.\n\nThis realizes the *error* category of the failure handling model defined in\n:need:`doc__nothrow_failure_handling`.", "docname": "nothrow/requirements/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__nothrow__alloc_fail", "lineno": 25, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "ASIL_B", "satisfies": ["feat_req__nothrow__container_utilities"], "section_name": "Requirements", "sections": ["Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "invalid", "title": "Nothrow allocation failure signaling", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__nothrow__asil": {"belongs_to": ["comp__baselibs_nothrow"], "content": "The ``score::nothrow`` library shall be ASIL-B compliant.", "docname": "nothrow/requirements/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__nothrow__asil", "lineno": 106, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "ASIL_B", "satisfies": ["feat_req__nothrow__container_utilities"], "section_name": "Safety Impact", "sections": ["Safety Impact"], "security": "NO", "status": "invalid", "title": "Nothrow library ASIL level", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__nothrow__create": {"belongs_to": ["comp__baselibs_nothrow"], "content": "Containers in ``score::nothrow`` shall provide explicit fallible factory\nfunctions that return ``score::Result<Container>`` for construction paths\nthat may require allocation.\n\nThis realizes the *error* category of the failure handling model defined in\n:need:`doc__nothrow_failure_handling`.", "docname": "nothrow/requirements/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__nothrow__create", "lineno": 41, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "ASIL_B", "satisfies": ["feat_req__nothrow__container_utilities"], "section_name": "Requirements", "sections": ["Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "invalid", "title": "Nothrow fallible construction", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__nothrow__mutate_result": {"belongs_to": ["comp__baselibs_nothrow"], "content": "Container operations that may allocate during mutation shall provide\nexplicit error-propagating APIs using ``score::Result`` or\n``score::ResultBlank`` instead of relying on exception-based failure\nsignaling.\n\nThis realizes the *error* category of the failure handling model defined in\n:need:`doc__nothrow_failure_handling`.", "docname": "nothrow/requirements/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__nothrow__mutate_result", "lineno": 57, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "ASIL_B", "satisfies": ["feat_req__nothrow__container_utilities"], "section_name": "Requirements", "sections": ["Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "invalid", "title": "Nothrow explicit mutation error propagation", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__nothrow__or_abort": {"belongs_to": ["comp__baselibs_nothrow"], "content": "For operations with explicit error-propagating APIs, ``score::nothrow``\nshall provide clearly named ``OrAbort`` convenience variants for cases where\nallocation failure is considered a programming error.\n\nThis realizes the *violation* category of the failure handling model defined\nin :need:`doc__nothrow_failure_handling`.", "docname": "nothrow/requirements/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__nothrow__or_abort", "lineno": 74, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "ASIL_B", "satisfies": ["feat_req__nothrow__container_utilities"], "section_name": "Requirements", "sections": ["Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "invalid", "title": "Nothrow aborting convenience operations", "type": "comp_req", "type_name": "Component Requirement"}, "comp_req__nothrow__pointer_policy": {"belongs_to": ["comp__baselibs_nothrow"], "content": "``score::nothrow`` containers shall store persisted internal pointers\nthrough a selectable pointer-slot policy abstraction so that storage\nsemantics can be changed without rewriting the container algorithms.", "docname": "nothrow/requirements/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp_req__nothrow__pointer_policy", "lineno": 90, "reqtype": "Functional", "safety": "ASIL_B", "satisfies": ["feat_req__nothrow__container_utilities"], "section_name": "Requirements", "sections": ["Requirements"], "security": "NO", "status": "invalid", "title": "Nothrow pointer-slot policy abstr